    "client_msg_id": "5BB52BDE-BE5E-49EE-9DED-F25393231203",
    "text": "Do you think there is something that is structurally difficult about building a Notion or an Airtable? In the sense of economics or even something like cultural values? People say it’s differentiated on design, but I suspect that there are many people who could design/build products like that, and there’s some other, invisible hurdle that those companies overcame.",
